            <div class="vtbegenerated" style="font-family: &quot;Open
              Sans&quot;, sans-serif; text-shadow: none !important;
              letter-spacing: normal !important; overflow-x: auto;
              padding: 0px !important; margin: 0px !important;
              background: transparent !important; font-size: 10pt;
              display: block; position: relative; overflow-wrap:
              break-word;">
              <h1 id="anonymous_element_16" style="font-family: arial,
                helvetica, sans-serif; text-shadow: none !important;
                letter-spacing: normal !important; margin: 1em 0px;
                padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight:
                bold; font-style: inherit; font-size: 19.7333px;"><span
                  style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                  text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                  !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                  outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style:
                  inherit; font-size: small;">The realization that not a
                  single country, no matter how powerful, can fight
                  organized crime across borders in isolation, led to
                  the passage of the <a
href="https://www.unodc.org/documents/treaties/UNTOC/Publications/TOC%20Convention/TOCebook-e.pdf"
                    target="_blank" style="font-family: arial,
                    helvetica, sans-serif; text-shadow: none !important;
                    letter-spacing: normal !important; margin: 0px;
                    padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px;
                    font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;
                    font-size: 13px; color: rgb(24, 116, 164);
                    text-decoration: underline;">United Nations
                    Convention against Transnational Organized Crime</a> (Organized
                  Crime Convention), which came into force in 2003. The
                  negotiations leading up to this Convention caused
                  Member States to consider the definition of organized
                  crime in setting the stage for international action.</span></h1>
              <div class="vtbegenerated_div" style="font-family: arial,
                helvetica, sans-serif; text-shadow: none !important;
                letter-spacing: normal !important; position: relative;
                overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-bottom: 1em;">The
                Convention does not contain a definition of
                transnational organized crime (TOC) or organized crime.
                There are many elements of organized crime, which might
                not occur in every case, and might also change over
                time, making a specific consensus definition difficult.
                Instead, the Convention defines "an organized criminal
                group." A precise definition is required because the
                Convention aims at directing policy, law, and practice
                in preventing and combating organized crime.</div>
              <div class="vtbegenerated_div" style="font-family: arial,
                helvetica, sans-serif; text-shadow: none !important;
                letter-spacing: normal !important; position: relative;
                overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-bottom: 1em;">Under
                the Convention (article 2a), an "<em style="font-family:
                  arial, helvetica, sans-serif; text-shadow: none
                  !important; letter-spacing: normal !important; margin:
                  0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px;
                  font-weight: inherit; font-style: italic; font-size:
                  13.3333px;"><strong style="font-family: arial,
                    helvetica, sans-serif; text-shadow: none !important;
                    letter-spacing: normal !important; margin: 0px;
                    padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px;
                    font-weight: bold; font-style: inherit; font-size:
                    13.3333px;">organized criminal group</strong></em>"
                is defined using four criteria:</div>
              <ul style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                !important; margin: 1em 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 40px;
                border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit;
                font-style: inherit; font-size: 13.3333px; list-style:
                disc;">
                <li style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                  text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                  !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                  outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style:
                  inherit; font-size: 13.3333px; display: list-item;
                  list-style-position: outside; list-style-type:
                  inherit;">A structured group of three or more persons;</li>
                <li style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                  text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                  !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                  outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style:
                  inherit; font-size: 13.3333px; display: list-item;
                  list-style-position: outside; list-style-type:
                  inherit;">The group exists for a period of time;</li>
                <li style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                  text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                  !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                  outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style:
                  inherit; font-size: 13.3333px; display: list-item;
                  list-style-position: outside; list-style-type:
                  inherit;">It acts in concert with the aim of
                  committing at least one serious crime;</li>
                <li style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                  text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                  !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                  outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style:
                  inherit; font-size: 13.3333px; display: list-item;
                  list-style-position: outside; list-style-type:
                  inherit;">To obtain, directly or indirectly, a
                  financial or other material benefit.</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="vtbegenerated_div" style="font-family: arial,
                helvetica, sans-serif; text-shadow: none !important;
                letter-spacing: normal !important; position: relative;
                overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-bottom: 1em;"><em
                  style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                  text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                  !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                  outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style:
                  italic; font-size: 13.3333px;"><strong
                    style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                    text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                    !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                    outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style:
                    inherit; font-size: 13.3333px;">Structured group</strong></em><span> </span>is
                defined in the negative: as one that does not need a
                formal hierarchy or continuity of its membership. This
                makes the definition broad, including loosely affiliated
                groups without any formally defined roles for its
                members or a developed structure.</div>
              <div class="vtbegenerated_div" style="font-family: arial,
                helvetica, sans-serif; text-shadow: none !important;
                letter-spacing: normal !important; position: relative;
                overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-bottom: 1em;">For
                purposes of the Convention,<span> </span><em
                  style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                  text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                  !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                  outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style:
                  italic; font-size: 13.3333px;"><strong
                    style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                    text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                    !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                    outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style:
                    inherit; font-size: 13.3333px;">serious crime</strong></em><span> </span>means
                an offence punishable by a maximum penalty of
                incarceration of at least four years (article 2b). Four
                years was selected by international consensus at the
                time of negotiation as a reflection of offence
                seriousness while it recognizes that criminal codes vary
                widely around the world in prescribing incarceration for
                various offences. There is no requirement for countries
                to introduce a definition of serious crime or to follow
                the definition of the Convention. The definition of
                serious crime is included to define the scope of
                application of the Convention and to invoke the
                international cooperation provisions of the Convention.</div>
              <div style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                !important;">The<span> </span><em style="font-family:
                  arial, helvetica, sans-serif; text-shadow: none
                  !important; letter-spacing: normal !important; margin:
                  0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px;
                  font-weight: inherit; font-style: italic; font-size:
                  13.3333px;"><strong style="font-family: arial,
                    helvetica, sans-serif; text-shadow: none !important;
                    letter-spacing: normal !important; margin: 0px;
                    padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px;
                    font-weight: bold; font-style: inherit; font-size:
                    13.3333px;">purpose</strong><span> </span></em>of
                organized criminal groups is "to obtain, directly or
                indirectly, a financial or other material benefit." It
                should be understood broadly. It includes, for example,
                crimes in which the predominant motivation may be sexual
                gratification, such as the receipt or trade of materials
                by members of child pornography rings, the trading of
                children by members of paedophile rings or cost sharing
                among ring members.</div>
              <div class="vtbegenerated_div" style="font-family: arial,
                helvetica, sans-serif; text-shadow: none !important;
                letter-spacing: normal !important; position: relative;
                overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span
                  style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                  text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                  !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                  outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style:
                  inherit; font-size: 13px;">The definitions make clear
                  that the size of an organized criminal group can be
                  quite small (although some organized criminal groups
                  can be large), and it does not have to exist for a
                  long period of time (although some do). Significantly,
                  the seriousness of the crimes committed by these
                  groups, and their profit-driven nature, are defining
                  elements.</span></div>
              <div class="vtbegenerated_div" style="font-family: arial,
                helvetica, sans-serif; text-shadow: none !important;
                letter-spacing: normal !important; position: relative;
                overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-bottom: 1em;">The
                Convention covers only<span> </span><strong
                  style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                  text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                  !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                  outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: inherit;
                  font-size: 13.3333px;"><em style="font-family: arial,
                    helvetica, sans-serif; text-shadow: none !important;
                    letter-spacing: normal !important; margin: 0px;
                    padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px;
                    font-weight: inherit; font-style: italic; font-size:
                    13.3333px;">transnational crimes</em></strong>,
                which are planned, executed, or have effects across
                national borders. This broad definition of
                transnationality acknowledges the complexity of the
                issue and sets the stage for broad international
                cooperation. The offence is<span> </span><em
                  style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                  text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                  !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                  outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style:
                  italic; font-size: 13.3333px;"><strong
                    style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                    text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                    !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                    outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style:
                    inherit; font-size: 13.3333px;">transnational</strong></em><span> </span>if:</div>
              <ul style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                !important; margin: 1em 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 40px;
                border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit;
                font-style: inherit; font-size: 13.3333px; list-style:
