                  substantial part of its preparation, planning,
                  direction or control takes place in another State;</li>
                <li style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                  text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                  !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                  outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style:
                  inherit; font-size: 13.3333px; display: list-item;
                  list-style-position: outside; list-style-type:
                  inherit;">It is committed in one State but involves an
                  organized criminal group that engages in criminal
                  activities in more than one State; or</li>
                <li style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                  text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                  !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                  outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style:
                  inherit; font-size: 13.3333px; display: list-item;
                  list-style-position: outside; list-style-type:
                  inherit;">It is committed in one State but has
                  substantial effects in another State. Source:  United
                  Nations Convention against Transnational Organized
                  Crime, article 3.2.</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="vtbegenerated_div" style="font-family: arial,
                helvetica, sans-serif; text-shadow: none !important;
                letter-spacing: normal !important; position: relative;
                overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span
                  style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;
                  text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal
                  !important; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;
                  outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style:
                  inherit; font-size: 13px;">Three protocols to the
                  Convention relate to specific types of transnational
                  crime: trafficking in persons, smuggling of migrants
                  and trafficking in firearms. These will be discussed
                  in other Guides as examples of transnational organized
                  crime that often involve multiple countries of origin,
                  transit and destination, and strongly require
                  concerted actions of these countries to respond or
                  prevent these crimes effectively.</span></div>
